============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is entropy?
A1: Entropy measures disorder or randomness in a system.
     The Second Law of Thermodynamics states it always
     increases in isolated systems — the arrow of time.

Q2: What is the water cycle?
A2: Water evaporates from oceans/lakes, rises and condenses
     into clouds, falls as precipitation, and flows back via
     rivers and groundwater. Driven by solar energy.

Q3: What is inflation?
A3: Inflation is the general rise in price levels over
     time, reducing purchasing power. Caused by excess money
     supply, high demand, or supply shocks. Measured by the
     Consumer Price Index.

Q4: What is evolution?
A4: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q5: What is relativity?
A5: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

